â†’ Runs ubuntu interactively in the terminal.
ğŸ“ 3. Containers vs Images
ğŸ–¼ Image

A read-only blueprint (like a recipe) used to create containers.

Stored in Local Hub (on your machine) or Docker Hub (online).

ğŸ“¦ Container

A running instance of an image.

Has its own filesystem, processes, and network.
When you delete a container, the image is not deleted â€” you can start another container from it anytime.

ğŸ“ 4. Deleting Containers vs Images
âŒ Delete a container:
